## #ComplianceKwanza Philosophy

All AI coding agents (Copilot, Cursor, Claude Sonnet, etc.) must adhere to the #ComplianceKwanza philosophy‚Äîsecurity, audit, compliance, and Tanzanian legal standards must be strictly followed in all code, documentation, and operational procedures. Reference PROJECT_CHARTER.md for strategic directives.

---

## Compliance Standards

- Mandatory reference to PROJECT_CHARTER.md before generating any code.
- All work must comply with GDPR-inspired, Tanzania Data Protection Act 2022, ISO 27001, OWASP Top 10, and WCAG 2.1 AA.
- Audit trail logging required for all code changes (minimum retention: 7 years).

---

## Security Standards

- Data at rest: AES-256 encryption.
- Data in transit: TLS 1.3 minimum.
- Authentication: JWT (30-min access, 7-day refresh), Bcrypt (‚â•12 rounds), MFA recommended.
- RBAC: Owner, Admin, Manager, User, Viewer.
- Rate limiting: All APIs must enforce per-role limits.
- Secrets: Never commit credentials, secrets, or keys.

---

## Code Generation Rules

- All files must begin with copyright header and timestamp.
- Documentation: All code, endpoints, database models must reference relevant documentation file (see README.md).
- Error handling: Use comprehensive try/catch, log all failures to audit trail.
- Bilingual support: All user-facing features must be documented for Swahili/English toggling.
- Accessibility: All UI output must meet WCAG 2.1 AA.
- Testing: Minimum 80% coverage, tests in both backend and frontend.
- No forbidden patterns: No hardcoded secrets, passwords, or API tokens.

---

## Response Formats

- API responses: Standardized success/error structure with bilingual messages.
- Audit log format: {timestamp, user_id, action, resource, status, details}

